<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,1015,1690]" pageId="23" pageNumber="314">
<bibRefCitation author="Schmidt, E." box="[151,328,1015,1042]" pageId="23" pageNumber="314" pagination="147 - 160" refId="ref15770" refString="Schmidt, E. (1927) Neue Zikaden-Gattungen und Arten. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, Berlin, 91, 147 - 160." type="journal article" year="1927">Schmidt (1927)</bibRefCitation>
described the species without any illustration. He did not dissect the type specimen but mention some male attributes. We provide here, the description and illustration of male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1141,1292,1051,1078]" captionStart="FIGURES 103–108" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1915,1940]" captionTargetBox="[177,1414,177,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[164,1423,170,1904]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 103–108. Poeciloterpa montana, holotype. 103. Male terminalia, lateral view. 104. Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. 105. Subgenital plate, lateral view, LP: lateral plate. 106. Paramere, lateral view. 107. Aedeagus, lateral view, ae: apical extension, pp: posterior protrusion, 108. Tegmina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3056002/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="314">Fig. 103–107</figureCitation>
) of the 
<typeStatus pageId="23" pageNumber="314">holotype</typeStatus>
and photographs of the habitus with the labels (
<figureCitation box="[737,882,1087,1114]" captionStart="FIGURES 99–102" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1577,1602]" captionTargetBox="[163,1425,341,1558]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[163,1425,341,1565]" captionText="FIGURES 99–102. Poeciloterpa montana, holotype. 99. Habitus, dorsal view. 100. frontal view. 101. lateral view. 102. Labels. Photographed by Laurent Fauvre © 2017 MNHN." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3404715/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="314">Figs 99–102</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="314" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,1015,1690]" pageId="23" pageNumber="314">
Male terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[392,491,1123,1150]" captionStart="FIGURES 103–108" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1915,1940]" captionTargetBox="[177,1414,177,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[164,1423,170,1904]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 103–108. Poeciloterpa montana, holotype. 103. Male terminalia, lateral view. 104. Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. 105. Subgenital plate, lateral view, LP: lateral plate. 106. Paramere, lateral view. 107. Aedeagus, lateral view, ae: apical extension, pp: posterior protrusion, 108. Tegmina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3056002/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="314">Fig. 103</figureCitation>
). In lateral view, pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[786,881,1123,1150]" captionStart="FIGURES 103–108" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1915,1940]" captionTargetBox="[177,1414,177,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[164,1423,170,1904]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 103–108. Poeciloterpa montana, holotype. 103. Male terminalia, lateral view. 104. Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. 105. Subgenital plate, lateral view, LP: lateral plate. 106. Paramere, lateral view. 107. Aedeagus, lateral view, ae: apical extension, pp: posterior protrusion, 108. Tegmina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3056002/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="314">Fig. 104</figureCitation>
) dorsal margin longer than ventral margin, dorsal margin almost straight with small hump in anterior part, ventral margin regularly curved, posterior margin undulated with clear hump in middle, posterodorsal angle rounded. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[979,1074,1195,1222]" captionStart="FIGURES 103–108" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1915,1940]" captionTargetBox="[177,1414,177,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[164,1423,170,1904]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 103–108. Poeciloterpa montana, holotype. 103. Male terminalia, lateral view. 104. Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. 105. Subgenital plate, lateral view, LP: lateral plate. 106. Paramere, lateral view. 107. Aedeagus, lateral view, ae: apical extension, pp: posterior protrusion, 108. Tegmina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3056002/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="314">Fig. 105</figureCitation>
) in lateral view pointing straight posteriorly, thick with broadest part at mid length, gradually tapering towards a pointed apex curving up; lateral plate leaf-shaped pointing anteroventrally, intermediate plate absent. Paramere (
<figureCitation box="[1077,1176,1267,1294]" captionStart="FIGURES 103–108" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1915,1940]" captionTargetBox="[177,1414,177,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[164,1423,170,1904]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 103–108. Poeciloterpa montana, holotype. 103. Male terminalia, lateral view. 104. Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. 105. Subgenital plate, lateral view, LP: lateral plate. 106. Paramere, lateral view. 107. Aedeagus, lateral view, ae: apical extension, pp: posterior protrusion, 108. Tegmina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3056002/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="314">Fig. 106</figureCitation>
) largely rounded with dorsal margin curving ventrally into a fold, ventral margin curved subapically then straight prior to rounded part, dorsal and ventral apex angled nearly rectangular directed posteriorly, set of very short setae located at dorsal and ventral margin of paramere and oriented dorsoposteriorly. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[943,1040,1375,1402]" captionStart="FIGURES 103–108" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1915,1940]" captionTargetBox="[177,1414,177,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[164,1423,170,1904]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 103–108. Poeciloterpa montana, holotype. 103. Male terminalia, lateral view. 104. Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. 105. Subgenital plate, lateral view, LP: lateral plate. 106. Paramere, lateral view. 107. Aedeagus, lateral view, ae: apical extension, pp: posterior protrusion, 108. Tegmina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3056002/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="314">Fig. 107</figureCitation>
) with dorsal margin curving down then abruptly curving dorsally making a narrow angle then curving smoothly dorsally up to a stout apical extension which is not curling on itself, posterior protrusion largely rounded with apex oriented posterodorsally, posteroventral protrusion absent, ventral margin curving regularly without any break.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
